Police in Nyeri County have tracked down members of a criminal gang said to be terrorising boda boda operators in Mathira Constituency.  Nyeri Police Commander Adiel Nyange said detectives had arrested two men in connection with the murder of eight people and recovered three stolen motorbikes.  Nyange said one of the suspects had confessed to the murders reported in March this year. Help us serve you better by completing our quick survey. “It has been a breakthrough in hunting down the criminals who we believe were involved in the killing of boda boda operators in the constituency,” he said.  Guard killed, coffee beans valued at Sh800,000 stolen  Gang targeting schools, hotels and bars killed 13 in last one year  Making of a murderer: How school principal planned and executed her husband’s killing  Police urged to probe murder of Kisii couple He noted that one of the suspects was arrested while in possession of a stolen motorbike.  “The suspects were arraigned in Nanyuki High Court where they were denied bond,” he said.  He asked the public to trust the police officers to carry out their duties.   In April, the murder of George Kariuki, a boda boda operator, led to protests, with over 3,000 motorbike riders from Mathira burned down his house in General China, Nyeri County.  The riders also stormed Karatina Level 4 Hospital and lynched one of the suspects while another escaped.   Murder Mystery: FBI joins investigations into the disappearance & murder of Bashir Mohammed  Police detain a couple and their son for allegedly beating their 15-year-old daughter to death  Several people injured in Bamburi after they were attacked by gangsters, two 17-year-old's arrested By Muriithi Mugo | 20 hours ago By Caroline Chebet | 2 days ago By Muriithi Mugo | 2 days ago By Fidelis Kabunyi | 4 days ago